    <text id="F8038T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Reilly discusses local politics in Franklin County.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1854-10-02"><abbr expan="October">Oct.</abbr> 2d/<abbr
                                expan="1854">54</abbr></date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Simon">S.</abbr> Cameron<lb/>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You must excuse me for not answering your letter at an earlier day. You have no
                    doubt seen our nominations. They are good men and if elected I think one of them
                    at least would be your friend and vote for you. <abbr expan="Colonel"
                    >Col.</abbr> Orr is a Mason. Could you do any thing for me by writing to some
                    friend in <unclear>Quimata</unclear>, as also one or two in Adams. I will be
                    grateful for any assistance you can render me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours &amp;C</salute>
                    <signed>W. Reilly</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
